  "prompt": "What does it mean to have a dream about your best friend dying?",
  "response": "Dreams about a friend dying can be distressing, but they rarely predict actual death. Psychological interpretations suggest such dreams might symbolize:\n\n1. Fear of losing the friendship\n\u2022 Anxiety about growing apart\n\u2022 Concerns about changing relationship dynamics\n\n2. Personal transformation\n\u2022 Symbolic representation of changes in your friendship\n\u2022 Representing end of a certain phase of your relationship\n\n3. Emotional processing\n\u2022 Subconscious working through relationship anxieties\n\u2022 Reflection of deep emotional connections\n\n4. Personal insecurities\n\u2022 Fears about your own mortality\n\u2022 Unresolved feelings or unaddressed emotional issues\n\n5. Stress or recent life changes\n\u2022 Unconscious manifestation of personal stress\n\u2022 Symbolic representation of significant life transitions\n\nDream interpretations are highly personal, and the specific meaning can vary based on individual experiences and emotions. While unsettling, such dreams typically don't indicate a literal prediction of death.\n\nIf the dream causes significant distress, consider:\n\u2022 Talking to the friend\n\u2022 Exploring underlying emotions\n\u2022 Consulting a therapist for deeper insight\n\nRemember, dreams are complex and often reflect our inner psychological landscape rather than literal events.",
